						<p>Cookies information: When you visit the Service, we or our vendors may send one or more cookies - a small text file containing a string of alphanumeric characters - to your computer that uniquely identifies your browser and lets Creative Comments help you log in faster and enhance your navigation through the site. A cookie may also convey information to us about how you use the Service, and allow us to track your usage of the Service over time. We currently only employ cookies that are immediately removed from your computer after you login to Creative Comments. These cookies direct you to the appropriate video or link when you click on a link to www.creativecommenst.cc from a third-party location such as email, Facebook or Twitter. If you do not log into Creative Comments after clicking on an Creative Comments link, the cookie may remain on your computer for a maximum of 90 minutes.</p>
						<p>You can reset your web browser to refuse all cookies or to indicate when a cookie is being sent. However, some features of the Service may not function properly if the ability to accept cookies is disabled. How to enable and disable cookies using your browser:</p>
						<h4>Google Chrome</h4>
